WEBVTT

00:07.703 --> 00:10.619
♪♪

00:10.662 --> 00:12.055
Meredith: Our bodies play host

00:12.099 --> 00:15.015
to trillions of bacteria
and other microbes.

00:15.058 --> 00:18.148
They live on our skin,
in our guts, up our noses.

00:18.192 --> 00:20.063
Alright, the kids are
cleaning their rooms.

00:20.107 --> 00:21.238
[ Snaps fingers ]
What's next?

00:21.282 --> 00:24.024
Uh, appetizers, salad?
Anything.

00:24.067 --> 00:25.634
I should've taken
this whole day off.

00:25.677 --> 00:28.158
Microbes are found in almost
every part of the body.

00:28.202 --> 00:29.159
It doesn't need to
be perfect.

00:29.203 --> 00:30.291
It's just dinner.

00:30.334 --> 00:32.206
It's a dinner party
to welcome Nick.

00:32.249 --> 00:33.511
You know what?

00:33.555 --> 00:35.165
I don't remember getting
a welcome dinner party.

00:35.209 --> 00:36.558
You arrived
during a pandemic.

00:36.601 --> 00:38.255
Plus, Nick is very important
to Meredith,

00:38.299 --> 00:39.909
and I want to
get to know him.

00:39.952 --> 00:40.823
[ Cellphone chimes ]Mm-hmm.
You want to grill him.

00:40.866 --> 00:42.738
That's what you wanna do.

00:42.781 --> 00:43.956
Hospital?

00:44.000 --> 00:45.784
[ Sighs ] Hotel.

00:45.828 --> 00:48.091
Wendell's room service
is on the way.

00:48.135 --> 00:49.658
How's he doing?

00:49.701 --> 00:51.051
Apparently
living it up.

00:51.094 --> 00:52.139
On my dime.

00:52.182 --> 00:53.705
At least we got
our couch back.

00:53.749 --> 00:56.186
So when's he supposed to hear
about that job in Boston?

00:56.230 --> 00:57.579
Well, he says
any day now.

00:57.622 --> 00:59.015
[ Beeping ]

00:59.059 --> 01:00.277
Oh, do you want me
to slice these?

01:00.321 --> 01:01.887
No, Amelia's
gonna make guacamole.

01:01.931 --> 01:03.150
Where is Amelia?

01:03.193 --> 01:05.456
Microbes help us
produce vitamins

01:05.500 --> 01:07.850
and stimulate
our immune system.

01:07.893 --> 01:09.069
♪♪

01:09.112 --> 01:10.592
Wow.
[ Breathes deeply ]

01:10.635 --> 01:12.420
That was...

01:12.463 --> 01:14.726
Better than forcing me
to go sight-seeing?

01:14.770 --> 01:17.120
Ah. I don't know.

01:17.164 --> 01:20.645
The view from the Space Needle
is pretty spectacular.

01:20.689 --> 01:22.430
Hmm. More
spectacular than this?

01:22.473 --> 01:25.433
You can see Mount Rainier...
[ Sighs ]

01:25.476 --> 01:29.654
...Puget Sound,
Meredith's house --

01:29.698 --> 01:32.266
♪ Turn it out,
give 'em what they came for ♪

01:32.309 --> 01:33.702
We're late.
We g-- we gotta go.

01:33.745 --> 01:36.531
Maggie is gonna freak out.
We gotta go.
Hey. Hey.

01:36.574 --> 01:38.533
♪ Just tell me
the place and time ♪

01:38.576 --> 01:40.274
You sure?

01:40.317 --> 01:42.145
They break down food and
perform many other functions

01:42.189 --> 01:43.755
that we need to survive.

01:43.799 --> 01:45.496
Nope.♪ Make it look like
I never try ♪

01:45.540 --> 01:47.716
♪ Now shake it, shake it,
watch me move ♪

01:47.759 --> 01:48.934
[ Telephone rings in distance,
indistinct conversations ]

01:48.978 --> 01:50.414
Hey.
Hey.

01:50.458 --> 01:51.720
I thought you
had a transplant.

01:51.763 --> 01:52.895
No, I'm all done.

01:52.938 --> 01:54.244
Ms. Olick is in the ICU.

01:54.288 --> 01:55.637
I'm gonna
drop by my place

01:55.680 --> 01:57.117
and then I'm gonna
head to yours.Okay.

01:57.160 --> 01:58.422
I just have one more patient
and then I'll see you there.

01:58.466 --> 01:59.554
Okay.Okay.

01:59.597 --> 02:01.686
-What?
-No, it's nice.

02:01.730 --> 02:03.427
Just living in the same city.
I like it. It's nice.

02:03.471 --> 02:05.647
Well, hopefully you feel
the same way after tonight.

02:05.690 --> 02:07.388
[ Chuckles ] If you're
trying to scare me off,

02:07.431 --> 02:09.085
it's gonna take a lot more than
your sisters and your kids.

02:09.129 --> 02:12.001
Promise me you won't get home
and decide to skip the party.

02:12.044 --> 02:13.350
And miss the awkward
small talk?

02:13.394 --> 02:14.612
Never.
[ Laughs ]

02:14.656 --> 02:15.657
See ya.

02:15.700 --> 02:17.093
You're still here?

02:17.137 --> 02:18.529
Don't tell me
the party is canceled.Wow.

02:18.573 --> 02:21.141
I got all the senior residents
working, a babysitter.

02:21.184 --> 02:22.838
I got my party shoes
in the car.

02:22.881 --> 02:24.448
Do not ruin this
for me.

02:24.492 --> 02:26.624
Bailey, the party is
not canceled.

02:26.668 --> 02:27.799
I will see you there.
Good.

02:27.843 --> 02:29.366
Look at my face.

02:29.410 --> 02:30.498
I need fun.

02:30.541 --> 02:32.195
Me too.

02:34.154 --> 02:35.851
Ay, yi, yi, yi.

02:36.460 --> 02:39.246
ABG looks good.
Patient's less acidotic.

02:39.289 --> 02:41.073
You want me to run
another one in an hour?

02:41.117 --> 02:42.292
No, no.
You should go home.

02:42.336 --> 02:44.381
I don't want your hours
to become a problem

02:44.425 --> 02:46.253
for the Medical
Accreditation Council, hm?
Mm.

02:46.296 --> 02:48.559
Why aren't you
in party clothes?

02:48.603 --> 02:50.431
[ Breathes sharply ]
You have chemo.

02:50.474 --> 02:51.910
Yes, Ihave chemo.

02:51.954 --> 02:53.216
Youhave a party.

02:53.260 --> 02:54.783
A dinner party.

02:54.826 --> 02:56.567
Look, I promised
if you did this trial

02:56.611 --> 02:59.179
that I would stand by your side
for every step.

02:59.222 --> 03:01.746
Baby, you went with me
to my first infusion.

03:01.790 --> 03:03.618
I'll be fine
by myself.

03:03.661 --> 03:06.664
I'm not breaking
my promise.

03:06.708 --> 03:11.887
♪♪

03:11.930 --> 03:15.064
♪♪

03:15.107 --> 03:16.196
[ Door opens ]

03:16.239 --> 03:17.371
♪♪

03:17.414 --> 03:19.242
We're here!

03:19.286 --> 03:20.809
Everyone, this is Kai.[ Door closes ]

03:20.852 --> 03:23.028
Hi!
Nice to meet you.

03:23.072 --> 03:25.509
I'm Maggie.
I'm Amelia's sister.

03:25.553 --> 03:26.815
This is Winston,
my husband.
Winston: Hey.

03:26.858 --> 03:27.990
-Ooh!
-Ooh!

03:28.033 --> 03:29.252
Sorry!

03:29.296 --> 03:31.646
And this is
Zola, Bailey, and Ellis.

03:31.689 --> 03:32.777
-Hi!
-Hi!
-Hi!

03:32.821 --> 03:33.778
Sorry we're late.

03:33.822 --> 03:34.823
It was my fault.

03:34.866 --> 03:36.346
Maggie: Oh.

03:36.390 --> 03:37.913
[ Mouths word ]Winston: Hi. Nice to meet you.

03:37.956 --> 03:39.306
Uh, put -- put us to work.
Uh, how can we help?

03:39.349 --> 03:40.394
Did you bring the ice?

03:40.437 --> 03:41.699
Ah. [ Chuckles ]

03:41.743 --> 03:43.266
-Alright, I'll go pick that up.
-Thank you.

03:43.310 --> 03:45.137
Yeah.
What else can we help with?

03:45.181 --> 03:46.138
Oh.Zola: Hey, that's mine.

03:46.182 --> 03:47.662
No, it's not.
Yes, it is.

03:47.705 --> 03:48.924
It's not.

03:48.967 --> 03:50.621
Can you keep them from
breaking each other?

03:50.665 --> 03:51.970
Hey, guys!

03:52.014 --> 03:53.711
Why don't we take
this party outside?

03:53.755 --> 03:55.670
Yes!
Yeah!

03:55.713 --> 03:56.801
You play soccer?

03:56.845 --> 03:58.890
I was hoping
that you do.

03:58.934 --> 04:00.414
[ Doorbell rings ]

04:00.457 --> 04:01.632
[ Indistinct conversation ]

04:01.676 --> 04:02.894
Come on.

04:04.418 --> 04:05.680
[ Chuckles ]
Hey.

04:05.723 --> 04:06.985
Aww.

04:07.029 --> 04:07.986
Is that how we
greet our guests?

04:08.030 --> 04:09.727
I thought it was Mama.

04:09.771 --> 04:11.033
Aww.I'm sorry.

04:11.076 --> 04:12.556
-Come in. Come on in.
-Okay. Yep.

04:12.600 --> 04:14.341
Um, Meredith
isn't here yet, obviously.Okay. Yeah.

04:14.384 --> 04:16.995
And you are on time
to the minute.

04:17.039 --> 04:18.519
Yeah, it's
a transplant surgeon thing.

04:18.562 --> 04:19.781
If I'm late,
organs die, so...

04:19.824 --> 04:21.130
Yeah.
Here you go.

04:21.173 --> 04:22.566
Oh, thank you so much.
Welcome.

04:22.610 --> 04:24.176
Yeah, well, I wanted to bring
flowers, but Meredith said

04:24.220 --> 04:25.917
that only stresses out the host,
because then they're

04:25.961 --> 04:27.919
forced to find a vase
and put water in it, so...

04:27.963 --> 04:29.007
Listen,
wine is always welcome.

04:29.051 --> 04:30.531
Okay. Good.
[ Chuckles ]

04:30.574 --> 04:33.055
So, uhh, Winston is
out getting ice,

04:33.098 --> 04:34.491
and I'm a little behind
on the food.
Oh, okay.

04:34.535 --> 04:35.927
So, uh, make yourself at home,
and I --
Yeah, okay.

04:35.971 --> 04:37.973
[ Doorbell rings ]
Oh.

04:38.016 --> 04:40.062
[ Breathes deeply ]

04:41.237 --> 04:42.673
-Hey!
-Hey!
-Hey!

04:42.717 --> 04:44.936
It's customary to be
at least 15 minutes late!

04:44.980 --> 04:46.373
We could wait outside,
or --
No, no, no.

04:46.416 --> 04:47.591
Come in, come in.
[ Chuckles ]

04:47.635 --> 04:48.853
Hey!
Hi.

04:48.897 --> 04:50.333
Uh --
should I open these?

04:50.377 --> 04:51.291
I'll take the two of them.Oh, of course.

04:51.334 --> 04:52.683
No! No, he can't.No, no, no.

04:52.727 --> 04:54.337
It's alright. It's alright.
Um, who's not on call?

04:54.381 --> 04:55.730
Me.
[ Laughter ]

04:55.773 --> 04:56.818
-Alright. Mm-hmm.
-Come on in.

04:57.645 --> 04:59.168
[ Siren wails ]

04:59.211 --> 05:00.952
Well, good night, Dr. Grey.
Have fun at your party.

05:00.996 --> 05:01.736
[ Air brakes hiss ]It's just a dinner.

05:01.779 --> 05:03.215
Well, it's not work.

05:03.259 --> 05:04.826
[ Chuckles ] Fair point.[ Ambulance doors open ]

05:04.869 --> 05:06.915
Plus, it gives the residents
a chance to step up and help.

05:06.958 --> 05:08.395
I remember
having that attitude.

05:08.438 --> 05:09.700
[ Groaning ]

05:09.744 --> 05:11.920
Alice Tom. 72.
Massive facial trauma

05:11.963 --> 05:13.574
and complaining of right arm
and abdominal pain

05:13.617 --> 05:14.792
after an assault
at a bus stop.

05:14.836 --> 05:15.880
Oh, my God.

05:15.924 --> 05:18.361
Tachy in the 120s,
BP 140 over 90.

05:18.405 --> 05:19.623
She received 4 of morphine
en route.

05:19.667 --> 05:21.016
Okay,
let's get her inside.What happened?

05:21.059 --> 05:23.018
Bus driver said the attacker
was using racial slurs

05:23.061 --> 05:24.367
and yelling at her to
go back to where she's from.

05:24.411 --> 05:25.673
Oh, my God.
Okay.

05:25.716 --> 05:27.588
We've got you, Alice.[ Alice groaning ]

05:40.122 --> 05:44.256
Oh, UCSF's starting trials
on a new treatment.

05:44.300 --> 05:45.867
Maybe we should
look into it, huh?

05:45.910 --> 05:47.259
Maybe. [ Sighs ]

05:47.303 --> 05:49.784
Does your oncologist come
to all your appointments?

05:49.827 --> 05:51.612
This is my husband.

05:51.655 --> 05:54.484
He's not my oncologist,
but he is a doctor.

05:54.528 --> 05:57.705
One who cares very much
about your health.

05:57.748 --> 05:59.794
Mm.
Hm.

05:59.837 --> 06:01.622
Chondrosarcoma.

06:01.665 --> 06:03.841
Synovial sarcoma.

06:03.885 --> 06:05.321
Hmm, that's tough.

06:05.365 --> 06:07.062
We like to say
it's persistent.

06:07.105 --> 06:09.281
You.You like to say
it's persistent.

06:09.325 --> 06:11.458
He's being exceedingly
optimistic.

06:11.501 --> 06:12.589
For me.

06:12.633 --> 06:13.895
How much longer?

06:13.938 --> 06:15.070
I'm 35 weeks and...

06:15.113 --> 06:16.637
Not that she's counting.

06:16.680 --> 06:17.986
No, of course
I'm counting.

06:18.029 --> 06:19.640
You have to be able
to meet him.

06:19.683 --> 06:21.555
Richard: Oh, nanotechnology's
come a long way.

06:21.598 --> 06:23.034
Maybe we should
look into that.

06:23.078 --> 06:25.210
Maybe.
Mm.

06:25.254 --> 06:27.691
So, have you two
picked out a name yet?

06:27.735 --> 06:29.476
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
on PA]

06:29.519 --> 06:31.129
Please tell me everything.

06:31.173 --> 06:33.480
I need a distraction.

06:33.523 --> 06:36.091
[ Alice groaning ]

06:36.134 --> 06:38.398
Michelle: Sorry.
I know it hurts.

06:38.441 --> 06:39.834
Push another
2 of morphine.

06:39.877 --> 06:41.749
[ Groaning continues ]

06:43.751 --> 06:46.275
She has a comminuted mid-shaft
humerus fracture

06:46.318 --> 06:47.624
with a wound over
the fracture site.

06:47.668 --> 06:51.236
♪♪

06:51.280 --> 06:52.803
It was a hate crime,
wasn't it?

06:52.847 --> 06:54.152
It appears that way.

06:54.196 --> 06:55.937
[ Groaning continues ]

06:55.980 --> 06:58.113
Meredith: We can get another
ortho surgeon --

06:58.156 --> 07:00.985
No, no, no, no. I'm here.
I'm -- I'll do it.

07:01.029 --> 07:03.553
I'd like
a maxillofacial scan.

07:03.597 --> 07:06.121
I am seeing some fluid
in the upper left quadrant.

07:06.164 --> 07:08.602
Let's order a CT to rule out
any other injuries.

07:08.645 --> 07:10.255
I'll call CT.

07:10.299 --> 07:12.170
Okay, I'll clean out
this fracture wound

07:12.214 --> 07:13.345
as soon as you're done
with your evaluation.

07:13.389 --> 07:14.738
Let's get her started
on antibiotics

07:14.782 --> 07:16.000
and just page me
as soon as you're done.

07:16.044 --> 07:17.045
Please.

07:17.088 --> 07:18.916
[ Groaning continues ]Okay.

07:18.960 --> 07:27.229
♪♪

07:27.272 --> 07:29.100
Right. Okay.

07:29.144 --> 07:30.188
Oh, may I?

07:30.232 --> 07:31.625
No, you are
the guest of honor.

07:31.668 --> 07:33.148
...who has impressive
knife skills.

07:33.191 --> 07:34.976
Please. I got it.[ Mouths word ]

07:35.019 --> 07:36.368
What? Oh. Hey!
I can help.

07:36.412 --> 07:38.762
Oh, uh...

07:38.806 --> 07:39.502
It's a salad.
[ Chuckles ]

07:39.546 --> 07:41.199
Right. [ Chuckles ]

07:41.243 --> 07:43.898
So, uh, how long
you been at the clinic?

07:43.941 --> 07:45.726
[ Knife chopping ][ Chuckles ]

07:45.769 --> 07:48.163
Um, about 16 years.

07:48.206 --> 07:49.817
I did my residency
in D.C. before that.

07:49.860 --> 07:51.383
You didn't
like the East Coast?

07:51.427 --> 07:52.776
No, I got a fellowship
back home,

07:52.820 --> 07:54.735
and, well, to be honest,

07:54.778 --> 07:56.867
my uh, sister couldn't stay
sober long enough

07:56.911 --> 07:58.565
to remember she had
a toddler.[ Door opens ]

07:58.608 --> 08:00.828
So, two birds,
one stone, I guess.[ Door closes ]

08:00.871 --> 08:02.133
[ Scoffs ]
That's probably
the wrong analogy,

08:02.177 --> 08:03.134
but you get the picture.

08:03.178 --> 08:04.353
Yeah.
You got kids?

08:04.396 --> 08:05.746
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Toddlers.

08:05.789 --> 08:06.747
Hey, I got ice.

08:06.790 --> 08:07.965
Nick, hey.
Hey.

08:08.009 --> 08:09.053
Welcome.Backyard cooler.

08:09.097 --> 08:10.490
Alright.

08:10.533 --> 08:12.317
Hey, where does Mer
keep the games?

08:12.361 --> 08:13.841
Games?
It's a dinner party.

08:13.884 --> 08:16.408
Well, I mean --
is dinner ready?

08:16.452 --> 08:18.802
[ Doorbell rings ]

08:18.846 --> 08:20.064
[ Chuckles ]

08:20.108 --> 08:21.544
[ Children laughing ]

08:21.588 --> 08:22.806
Hi. How are you?

08:22.850 --> 08:24.416
[ Fussing ]What's wrong?

08:24.460 --> 08:26.593
Oh, geopolitics
are a mess,

08:26.636 --> 08:28.420
global warming's
getting worse --

08:28.464 --> 08:29.509
You meant him.

08:29.552 --> 08:30.553
Yeah.
Yeah.

08:30.597 --> 08:31.859
I think he wants
Amelia.

08:31.902 --> 08:33.382
Oh, it's okay, buddy.[ Strained ] Here we go!

08:33.425 --> 08:35.210
Hey.
Ahh.

08:35.253 --> 08:36.428
It's okay.

08:36.472 --> 08:37.604
Hey, it's okay.

08:37.647 --> 08:40.084
-Hello.
-Hi.

08:40.128 --> 08:41.825
Food's in the kitchen,
drinks are out back.

08:41.869 --> 08:42.826
-Come on. Come with me.
-[ Sighs ]

08:42.870 --> 08:45.263
Go, I got him.

08:45.307 --> 08:48.223
[ Children laughing,
speaking indistinctly ]

08:48.266 --> 08:49.964
[ Door creaks ]

08:50.007 --> 08:54.142
♪♪

08:54.185 --> 08:55.665
Why didn't you say that?
Hold on. What does that mean?

08:55.709 --> 08:56.753
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:56.797 --> 08:58.581
Well, good evening,
Chief Bailey.

08:58.625 --> 08:59.974
Can I take your coat?

09:00.017 --> 09:01.628
How about a drink?

09:01.671 --> 09:02.803
[ Sighs ]Oh, Bailey!

09:02.846 --> 09:03.978
Want to play Boggle?

09:04.021 --> 09:05.806
[ Chuckling ]
I very much do not.

09:05.849 --> 09:07.677
Come on,
it's so much fun.

09:07.721 --> 09:09.374
You made me the ambassador
of fun, remember?

09:09.418 --> 09:11.463
Yeah, I never
understood that.

09:11.507 --> 09:13.944
Uh, Grey couldn't bother
to make it to her own party?

09:13.988 --> 09:15.859
Or set out a few crackers?

09:15.903 --> 09:17.600
Chief.

09:17.644 --> 09:18.993
Marsh.

09:19.036 --> 09:20.734
Yeah, Meredith is running
a bit late, but, uh --

09:20.777 --> 09:22.431
can I get you a drink,
glass of wine?

09:22.474 --> 09:23.563
Bourbon. Neat.

09:23.606 --> 09:24.999
And generous.

09:25.042 --> 09:26.391
Okay, I approve.[ Doorbell rings ]

09:26.435 --> 09:27.523
This way.

09:27.567 --> 09:29.090
Mm.

09:29.133 --> 09:30.526
No, no. I'm not playing
Boggle with you.

09:30.570 --> 09:33.268
[ Sighs ]

09:33.311 --> 09:34.356
I've been texting you
for like 10 minutes.

09:34.399 --> 09:35.531
What the hell
are you doing here?

09:35.575 --> 09:36.750
Having dinner?

09:36.793 --> 09:38.142
[ Inhales deeply ]
My lenders are after me.

09:38.186 --> 09:40.318
I couldn't stay
at the hotel.

09:40.362 --> 09:42.190
Wendell.
Maggie,
you look so nice!

09:42.233 --> 09:43.887
H-Here you go.

09:43.931 --> 09:45.193
Do you happen to have
room for one more?

09:45.236 --> 09:48.675
♪♪

09:54.985 --> 09:57.597
[ Breathes deeply ][ Whispering ]
I am so sorry.

09:57.640 --> 09:59.163
I never thought he would
just show up here.

09:59.207 --> 10:00.643
Did you tell him
we were having a party?

10:00.687 --> 10:02.123
No, I told him
I was goingto a party.

10:02.166 --> 10:03.777
That guy's
a walking sales pitch.

10:03.820 --> 10:05.213
I wonder what
he's selling them now.

10:05.256 --> 10:07.302
Maggie, please.
I will -- I'll ask him to go.

10:07.345 --> 10:08.520
No, no, I'm not
asking for that.

10:08.564 --> 10:10.000
No, I-I-I want to.

10:10.044 --> 10:11.306
I just -- I need
a minute to figure out

10:11.349 --> 10:13.656
how he doesn't make
a big scene about this.

10:13.700 --> 10:14.657
[ Timer beeping ]
Hey.

10:14.701 --> 10:16.659
Um, are you okay?

10:16.703 --> 10:18.139
Fine. Yeah.

10:18.182 --> 10:19.749
I'm not just talking about
tonight, Winston.

10:19.793 --> 10:21.751
I am worried
about you.[ Beeping continues ]

10:21.795 --> 10:24.101
About us.

10:24.145 --> 10:25.494
I know.

10:25.537 --> 10:26.974
Sorry,
the t-timer's still going.

10:27.017 --> 10:28.105
Yeah.
Yeah.

10:28.149 --> 10:30.499
[ Beeping continues ]

10:30.542 --> 10:31.848
[ Sighs ]

10:31.892 --> 10:33.545
[ Grill sizzling ]

10:35.635 --> 10:37.332
You into music?

10:37.375 --> 10:38.681
Do I like music?

10:38.725 --> 10:40.552
Yeah, I like music.

10:40.596 --> 10:43.077
Uh, unless you're asking me
to join your garage band.

10:43.120 --> 10:44.121
Then -- Then, no.

10:44.165 --> 10:45.557
No, I-I don't.

10:45.601 --> 10:47.124
Got it.

10:47.168 --> 10:50.562
What's your opinion
on contact sports?

10:50.606 --> 10:51.738
[ Laughs ]

10:51.781 --> 10:53.478
Uh, hard pass for kids,

10:53.522 --> 10:55.393
and I'm -- I'm more of
a running/cycling guy.

10:55.437 --> 10:57.482
Oh, yeah?Yeah.

10:57.526 --> 10:58.788
Mountain bike?

10:58.832 --> 11:01.051
Not a lot of mountains
in Minnesota.

11:01.095 --> 11:03.706
Ah, right.

11:03.750 --> 11:06.491
This back burner's been
finicky for over a year.[ Lighter clicking ]

11:06.535 --> 11:08.276
When Meredith was
in the hospital with COVID,

11:08.319 --> 11:10.539
it was me, Amelia,
and four kids living here.

11:10.582 --> 11:12.584
So...I grilled a lot.

11:12.628 --> 11:15.065
Right.

11:15.109 --> 11:17.111
So you and Amelia are --
are Scout's parents?

11:17.154 --> 11:18.416
Yep.

11:18.460 --> 11:20.201
♪♪

11:20.244 --> 11:21.637
You're probably
friends with Kai.

11:21.681 --> 11:23.726
[ Chuckling ] Friends?
I-I mean, not really.

11:23.770 --> 11:24.988
But, impressed, yes.

11:25.032 --> 11:26.642
Their -- Their work
has brought in

11:26.686 --> 11:28.731
some pretty amazing grants
to the clinic.

11:28.775 --> 11:30.951
There's a reason they work
with David Hamilton.

11:30.994 --> 11:32.387
♪♪

11:32.430 --> 11:33.910
So you're saying
my ex traded up.

11:33.954 --> 11:35.738
[ Chuckles ]
It's hard to say.

11:35.782 --> 11:37.261
I haven't known you
that long.

11:37.305 --> 11:38.741
♪♪

11:38.785 --> 11:39.960
I'm gonna need
more beer.

11:40.003 --> 11:42.136
[ Chuckles ]

11:42.179 --> 11:47.489
♪♪

11:47.532 --> 11:48.533
[ Sighs ]

11:48.577 --> 11:50.361
[ Buttons clicking ]

11:50.405 --> 11:51.536
[ Cellphone chimes ]

11:51.580 --> 11:53.016
♪♪

11:53.060 --> 11:55.671
[ Crying ]I know.

11:55.715 --> 11:57.499
Hey, we should, uh,
have a playdate soon.

11:57.542 --> 11:58.979
Yeah.
Your kids
play with Scout?

11:59.022 --> 12:00.154
Yeah, Amelia.

12:00.197 --> 12:01.285
I'd say that she's
their favorite aunt,

12:01.329 --> 12:02.373
but my sister
would be mad, so...

12:02.417 --> 12:03.374
Aunt?

12:03.418 --> 12:04.636
Unofficial.

12:04.680 --> 12:06.682
Mm, yeah, she was there
the day I got Leo.

12:06.726 --> 12:08.466
And she drove Teddy
to the hospital

12:08.510 --> 12:09.467
when we had
Allison, so...

12:09.511 --> 12:10.599
That's right.

12:10.642 --> 12:11.774
Aunt, okay.

12:11.818 --> 12:12.819
[ Crying continues ]Okay. He's overtired.

12:12.862 --> 12:14.168
Or overstimulated.

12:14.211 --> 12:15.735
I'm gonna -- I'm gonna
try and put him down.

12:15.778 --> 12:18.346
Ellis wants more sparkling
cider, and my drawing app froze.

12:18.389 --> 12:20.087
Oh, here. Let me
try to restart it.

12:20.130 --> 12:21.305
Would you mind?

12:23.046 --> 12:25.483
Oh, s-sure.
Yeah.

12:25.527 --> 12:26.746
Bailey.
Bailey.

12:28.573 --> 12:30.488
[ Dog barking in distance ]

12:32.186 --> 12:33.709
[ Crunching ]

12:33.753 --> 12:34.971
Mmm.

12:36.407 --> 12:38.627
Maggie couldn't have
made this spinach dip.

12:38.670 --> 12:40.281
She's a Boston girl.

12:40.324 --> 12:41.499
She knows better than to
put garlic salt instead of --

12:41.543 --> 12:43.066
Look, how bad is it?

12:43.110 --> 12:44.067
Well, you know, Nana Ante
only used sea salt,

12:44.111 --> 12:45.721
so the situation's
fairly dire,

12:45.765 --> 12:47.201
but we won't be
too loud about it.[ Door opens ]

12:47.244 --> 12:48.332
The lenders, Wendell.[ Door closes ]

12:48.376 --> 12:49.943
When you say that
they're after you,

12:49.986 --> 12:51.161
does that mean
physically, or --

12:51.205 --> 12:52.380
Nick: Oh, hey, man.
Can you tell Maggie

12:52.423 --> 12:53.773
the veggies have
another five minutes?

12:53.816 --> 12:54.948
Oh, yeah.
Yeah. Hi.

12:54.991 --> 12:56.427
Wendell Ndugu.
Hi.

12:56.471 --> 12:57.646
I'm Winston's brother.

12:57.689 --> 12:58.778
Ah. Nick Marsh.

12:58.821 --> 12:59.866
Everyone here related,
or...?

12:59.909 --> 13:00.910
Uh, Wendell's
just visiting.

13:00.954 --> 13:02.085
Got it.
Well, for now.

13:02.129 --> 13:03.434
Seattle's not so bad.

13:03.478 --> 13:04.740
Might be nice to
be around family.

13:04.784 --> 13:06.437
Sure.
Come on,
you love Boston.

13:06.481 --> 13:08.309
Youlove Boston.No one loves Boston.

13:08.352 --> 13:09.658
That's a fact. It's true.[ Laughter ]

13:09.701 --> 13:11.834
It's very true.

13:11.878 --> 13:13.270
[ Dog barking in distance ]

13:13.314 --> 13:14.924
[ Lowered voice ]
That can't be good.

13:14.968 --> 13:16.143
Winston: [ Lowered voice ] No,
I think it's just small talk.

13:16.186 --> 13:18.406
What if Nick is
a con man like Wendell?

13:18.449 --> 13:20.408
Because con men
only talk to each other?

13:20.451 --> 13:22.149
Because the only person
who has charmed me

13:22.192 --> 13:24.629
as much as your brother
is Nick Marsh.

13:24.673 --> 13:26.718
What about me?

13:26.762 --> 13:28.024
Wendell:
I haven't. Yeah, we're --
we're ahead of the curve.

13:28.068 --> 13:29.809
Nick: Okay.
And these...

13:29.852 --> 13:31.767
[ Siren wails in distance ]

13:31.811 --> 13:32.942
Officer: There's
the husband, right there.

13:32.986 --> 13:34.944
Perfect.
Thank you so much.

13:34.988 --> 13:36.772
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
on PA]

13:36.816 --> 13:38.382
Mr. Tom. Excuse me.

13:38.426 --> 13:40.297
Hey. Hi,
I'm Meredith Grey.

13:40.341 --> 13:41.995
Uh-huh.And this is Dr. Schmitt.

13:42.038 --> 13:44.388
We are part of the medical team
working on your wife.

13:44.432 --> 13:46.564
How is she?
Will she be okay?

13:46.608 --> 13:49.350
Uh, she has a -- she suffered
a pretty serious attack, sir.

13:49.393 --> 13:51.047
She's in surgery
right now.

13:51.091 --> 13:53.920
She has a broken arm
and some facial fractures,

13:53.963 --> 13:56.705
which our plastics and
orthopedic teams are working on.

13:56.748 --> 13:58.750
Okay.

13:58.794 --> 14:01.362
She also suffered an injury
to her spleen,

14:01.405 --> 14:03.973
which at this point,
opening up her abdomen

14:04.017 --> 14:05.409
could do
more harm than good.

14:05.453 --> 14:08.021
And the blood flow
to her organs is stable.

14:08.064 --> 14:10.501
Oftentimes,
these things heal themselves.

14:11.328 --> 14:13.069
We have a family dinner
every week.

14:13.113 --> 14:15.202
She went to the store
to buy chocolate syrup

14:15.245 --> 14:18.118
so the grandkids could have
sundaes for dessert.

14:18.161 --> 14:21.121
I said I'd drive her,
but she was an engineer

14:21.164 --> 14:22.905
for the city's
Transportation Department

14:22.949 --> 14:24.646
for 30 years
before she retired.

14:24.689 --> 14:27.475
[ Voice breaking ]
She insisted on taking the bus.

14:27.518 --> 14:28.650
♪♪

14:28.693 --> 14:30.391
When will I be able
to see her?

14:30.434 --> 14:32.393
♪♪

14:32.436 --> 14:34.656
Very soon.
And -- And I will let you know

14:34.699 --> 14:37.615
as soon as
she's out of surgery, okay?

14:37.659 --> 14:40.314
Can we get you anything?
Coffee or -- or more water?

14:40.357 --> 14:42.446
Uh, no, no, no.
I'm fine, thank you.

14:42.490 --> 14:45.188
But is there a way I can
tell Alice that I'm here?

14:45.232 --> 14:46.886
That we're all here?

14:46.929 --> 14:48.888
I want her to know
that she's not alone.

14:48.931 --> 14:49.976
Of course.

14:50.019 --> 14:52.152
I would be happy
to tell her that.

14:52.195 --> 14:54.284
And again, I'm -- I'm very sorry
that this has happened.Yeah.

14:54.328 --> 15:00.290
♪♪

15:00.334 --> 15:06.688
♪♪

15:06.731 --> 15:08.733
Ooh!
Simon: Kris?

15:08.777 --> 15:10.779
Ooh, that was weird.
[ Chuckles ]

15:10.822 --> 15:12.737
I'm sure it's nothing.

15:12.781 --> 15:14.957
Oh, honestly,
I hate puzzles.

15:15.001 --> 15:16.089
Why do we do them?

15:16.132 --> 15:17.829
You hate doingpuzzles.

15:17.873 --> 15:19.135
You love
having finished them.

15:19.179 --> 15:21.268
Mm, but at
what cost, babe?

15:21.311 --> 15:22.573
At what cost?
[ Chuckles ]

15:22.617 --> 15:24.053
Sweetheart, you know,
I was thinking --

15:24.097 --> 15:26.708
we should create
a wellness room at home.

15:26.751 --> 15:29.145
You know, with a yoga mat,
a meditation stool.

15:29.189 --> 15:30.712
Lord.

15:30.755 --> 15:32.105
Kristen: Yeah,
I did that, too.

15:32.148 --> 15:33.976
It's now a very
calming storage room

15:34.020 --> 15:35.891
for our golf clubs
and our luggage.

15:35.935 --> 15:36.892
[ Laughter ]

15:36.936 --> 15:37.893
Aah!

15:37.937 --> 15:38.894
What?
Contractions?

15:38.938 --> 15:40.287
Should be
too early for that.

15:40.330 --> 15:42.724
Maybe he's just kicking
because he hates puzzles, too.

15:42.767 --> 15:44.160
Maybe we should call
Dr. Wilson.

15:44.204 --> 15:46.075
W-Wilson's your OB, huh?

15:46.119 --> 15:47.685
Yeah,
she's checked in on us

15:47.729 --> 15:49.470
a few times
since we've been here.

15:49.513 --> 15:50.645
[ Groaning ]Page her, baby.

15:50.688 --> 15:51.994
Yeah, I am -- Okay.

15:52.038 --> 15:53.474
[ Groaning ]

15:53.517 --> 15:55.258
What if -- Ah!
What if --

15:55.302 --> 15:56.694
No, no, it's too
early for that.

15:56.738 --> 15:58.218
What if it's not?Richard: Nurse. Nurse.

15:58.261 --> 15:59.784
Ahh!

15:59.828 --> 16:01.134
Take some deep breaths.

16:01.177 --> 16:02.091
[ Groaning lightly ]

16:09.620 --> 16:11.579
[ Monitor beeping ]

16:11.622 --> 16:13.189
[ Suction gurgling ]

16:16.497 --> 16:22.590
♪♪

16:22.633 --> 16:28.378
♪♪

16:28.422 --> 16:33.253
♪ Who's gonna cut the rope?

16:33.296 --> 16:37.039
When I was a kid, I used to
stare at my face in the mirror

16:37.083 --> 16:38.867
and wonder if I could use
my mom's makeup

16:38.910 --> 16:41.391
to make me look
more "American,"

16:41.435 --> 16:44.699
which, of course, I understood
to mean more white.

16:44.742 --> 16:46.353
You wanted to be like
all the other kids.

16:46.396 --> 16:51.488
And my teachers and people I saw
in movies and on TV.

16:51.532 --> 16:53.012
I wanted to feel normal.

16:53.055 --> 16:54.709
Like I belonged.

16:54.752 --> 16:56.580
♪ Carry on

16:56.624 --> 17:00.280
Do you even think we'll ever
stop being seen as foreign?

17:00.323 --> 17:02.369
Well, being wrongly blamed
for COVID did not help.

17:02.412 --> 17:04.153
But also,
the Watsonville Riots.

17:04.197 --> 17:05.285
[ Sighs ]

17:05.328 --> 17:07.287
The Japanese American
internment.

17:07.330 --> 17:09.028
Vincent Chin.

17:09.071 --> 17:10.377
A long history
of being outsiders.

17:10.420 --> 17:12.640
How ironic.

17:12.683 --> 17:15.338
We areAmericans.

17:15.382 --> 17:17.645
♪ How do I drain
all of this bad blood? ♪

17:17.688 --> 17:19.473
Your face is American.

17:19.516 --> 17:25.957
♪♪

17:26.001 --> 17:28.221
[ Suction gurgling ]

17:28.264 --> 17:31.572
♪♪

17:31.615 --> 17:32.877
♪ I do the best I can

17:32.921 --> 17:34.096
Have her vitals
been stable?

17:34.140 --> 17:36.751
Uh, yeah,
she's okay for now.

17:36.794 --> 17:38.622
Okay.

17:38.666 --> 17:40.102
Do you mind if I...

17:40.146 --> 17:42.191
♪ Balancing on the edge

17:42.235 --> 17:43.932
Meredith: Alice,
your husband is here,

17:43.975 --> 17:46.108
and your whole family
is here.

17:46.152 --> 17:48.110
We're going to
take care of you.

17:48.154 --> 17:49.807
You're not alone.

17:49.851 --> 17:53.115
You are not alone, Alice.

17:53.159 --> 17:55.030
I'll check back in a bit.

17:55.074 --> 17:57.076
♪ Carry on

17:57.119 --> 17:58.555
I'm so sorry.

17:58.599 --> 18:01.036
♪ Carry on

18:01.080 --> 18:02.907
♪♪

18:02.951 --> 18:08.783
♪ What do you say
when your chance is gone? ♪

18:08.826 --> 18:11.960
♪ Fair enough

18:12.003 --> 18:14.658
♪ Fair enough

18:14.702 --> 18:16.443
I heard, and I didn't
want to go home.

18:16.486 --> 18:19.620
♪ How do I drain
all of this bad blood? ♪

18:19.663 --> 18:21.665
[ Crying ]
No one called for help.

18:21.709 --> 18:23.189
[ Breathes sharply ]

18:23.232 --> 18:25.756
No one intervened
or even took a video.

18:25.800 --> 18:30.805
♪♪

18:30.848 --> 18:32.807
It's so awful.
[ Breathes sharply ]

18:32.850 --> 18:35.940
♪♪

18:35.984 --> 18:39.553
And I just --
I wish I could help.

18:39.596 --> 18:41.903
[ Crying ]

18:41.946 --> 18:43.948
[ Vocalizing ]

18:43.992 --> 18:52.218
♪♪

18:52.261 --> 18:54.307
Jo: Okay.
Okay, Kristen.

18:54.350 --> 18:57.223
So, your contractions are
irregular and not too strong,

18:57.266 --> 19:00.139
so it appears to be
just Braxton Hicks.

19:00.182 --> 19:02.141
Doctors always say
"just" Braxton Hicks

19:02.184 --> 19:03.490
as though they
don't actually hurt.

19:03.533 --> 19:04.795
I know. I'm sorry.

19:04.839 --> 19:06.101
Doctors are the worst.

19:06.145 --> 19:07.189
Excuse me?

19:07.233 --> 19:09.365
Stop hovering.
Mind your business.

19:09.409 --> 19:10.845
Come over here.

19:10.888 --> 19:12.194
Thank you. We really
appreciate you taking a look.

19:12.238 --> 19:13.674
Of course.

19:13.717 --> 19:16.198
I do want to take you to OB
triage, do a cervical exam,

19:16.242 --> 19:18.113
and to monitor you
just for a bit in case.

19:18.157 --> 19:20.071
And we can see how the baby's
doing with the contractions.

19:20.115 --> 19:23.292
No, no.
I-I can't leave Simon.

19:23.336 --> 19:25.642
You'll just be upstairs,
and we can page if any--

19:25.686 --> 19:28.123
Please.
I don't want to be alone.

19:28.167 --> 19:29.864
Hey.
Catherine:
Richard, take her up.

19:29.907 --> 19:31.866
You've been cooped up here
all night long.

19:31.909 --> 19:34.869
Simon will keep me company,
and you and Kristen

19:34.912 --> 19:38.046
can go somewhere
where there are no puzzles.

19:38.089 --> 19:39.656
-[ Chuckles ]
-Please, babe.

19:39.700 --> 19:41.136
I don't want
you hurting, too.

19:42.485 --> 19:44.313
Okay.
Okay.

19:44.357 --> 19:45.445
Come with me.

19:45.488 --> 19:48.883
I'll be fine.
I promise.
Okay.

19:48.926 --> 19:51.451
This way.Promise.

19:51.494 --> 19:53.453
Woman on PA:
Dr. Williams to Radiology.

19:53.496 --> 19:55.890
Dr. Sandra Williams
to Radiology.

19:56.934 --> 19:58.936
[ Insects chirping in distance ]

20:01.330 --> 20:02.810
So, uh, Nick, what's
your favorite place

20:02.853 --> 20:04.420
to do a transplant?

20:04.464 --> 20:05.813
Oh, um, well,

20:05.856 --> 20:08.119
I put a pig's kidney on
a man's groin the other day.

20:08.163 --> 20:09.599
That was pretty fun.

20:09.643 --> 20:12.036
Uh, no.
Probably San Diego.

20:12.080 --> 20:13.864
It doesn't matter when you get
off work, you can always find...

20:13.908 --> 20:15.301
Tacos.
...tacos.

20:15.344 --> 20:16.519
Yes.

20:16.563 --> 20:17.999
Uh, I did a rotation
there in med school.

20:18.042 --> 20:19.043
UC San Diego?

20:19.087 --> 20:20.219
G.I. Department.

20:20.262 --> 20:22.090
Under Ned Powell.Ooh, Ned Powell.

20:22.133 --> 20:24.048
Incredible surgeon.
Terrible at cards.

20:24.092 --> 20:25.441
Uh, what about,
uh, board games?

20:25.485 --> 20:27.443
The people in this house
are fiercely competitive.

20:27.487 --> 20:29.532
[ Chuckles ]
Depends.

20:29.576 --> 20:30.403
Alright.
What about Scrabble?

20:30.446 --> 20:31.926
Sure.

20:31.969 --> 20:33.232
I mean, you know, that game
isn't so much about

20:33.275 --> 20:34.581
the vocabulary
as the math.

20:34.624 --> 20:36.800
Yeah, long, brainy words

20:36.844 --> 20:38.846
made up of one-point
A's, T's, and R's

20:38.889 --> 20:41.065
aren't nearly as good
as words like "X-ray."

20:41.109 --> 20:43.372
Yes, with the "X" on
a triple letter score.

20:43.416 --> 20:44.504
Correct.

20:44.547 --> 20:45.418
Ever try
cryptic crosswords?

20:45.461 --> 20:46.419
[ Chuckles ] No.

20:46.462 --> 20:48.290
How 'bout Boggle?

20:48.334 --> 20:50.031
Uh...

20:50.074 --> 20:51.641
[ Imitating train engine ]

20:51.685 --> 20:53.817
You know, I always wanted one
of these when I was a kid.

20:53.861 --> 20:55.602
I liked
the Y-shaped pieces --

20:55.645 --> 20:57.430
the idea that you could veer
off the main course

20:57.473 --> 20:58.779
but still be on track
intrigued me.

20:58.822 --> 21:00.302
Huh.

21:00.346 --> 21:02.086
You know, I-I just
thought trains were cool.

21:02.130 --> 21:03.697
[ Door opens ][ Both laugh ]

21:03.740 --> 21:05.829
I'm supposed to remind you there
are hiding people out there

21:05.873 --> 21:06.787
waiting for you
to seek them.

21:06.830 --> 21:08.179
Oh, yes. Okay.

21:08.223 --> 21:10.704
Scout?Oh, he's upstairs
with Amelia.

21:10.747 --> 21:12.488
Okay, good.
Coming!

21:12.532 --> 21:15.056
And after ten years of
studying...

21:15.099 --> 21:16.971
[ Door opens,
knock on door ]

21:17.014 --> 21:18.494
You having
your own party up here?

21:18.538 --> 21:20.104
Yeah.

21:20.148 --> 21:21.802
He's almost settled.

21:21.845 --> 21:23.369
Oh. You want me
to take him?

21:23.412 --> 21:25.501
Hm.
I could be
the closer.

21:25.545 --> 21:26.937
I'm pretty boring.

21:26.981 --> 21:28.939
I got him.

21:28.983 --> 21:30.419
I really don't mind.

21:30.463 --> 21:32.116
And you have a date.

21:32.160 --> 21:33.466
Hmm.

21:33.509 --> 21:35.729
It's okay.

21:35.772 --> 21:36.991
But thank you.

21:38.166 --> 21:39.602
Mm.

21:39.646 --> 21:43.171
"...patients with inoperable
plexiform neurofibromas

21:43.214 --> 21:45.608
showed durable
tumor shrinkage --"

21:45.652 --> 21:47.523
Are you reading
a medical journal?

21:49.046 --> 21:51.397
[ Breathes deeply ]
I can be boring, too.

21:51.440 --> 21:52.963
[ Breathes sharply ]

21:53.007 --> 21:55.270
"How does this nomogram
correlate with survival..."

21:56.619 --> 21:58.055
[ Laughter ]

21:58.099 --> 21:59.970
Hey.
Who was on the phone?

22:00.014 --> 22:01.276
No one.

22:01.320 --> 22:02.582
Uh,
is dinner ready?

22:04.235 --> 22:06.890
Uh -- Wendell.

22:06.934 --> 22:09.110
Hey, uh, I-I don't
think you should stay.

22:09.153 --> 22:10.764
Alright, um, I'll pack up
some food for you,

22:10.807 --> 22:11.721
but then you should
go back to the hotel.

22:11.765 --> 22:13.027
Alright?
Look.

22:13.070 --> 22:16.030
The people that I owe --

22:16.073 --> 22:18.206
they're not good people.

22:18.249 --> 22:19.642
They know you're here
in Seattle?

22:19.686 --> 22:22.210
Yes.
Wendell.

22:22.253 --> 22:24.647
But that's why I need to
disappear for a while.

22:24.691 --> 22:26.432
Look, I just wanted
to spend one more night

22:26.475 --> 22:28.390
with my big brother.
Hm.

22:28.434 --> 22:30.784
And ask for some cash.

22:30.827 --> 22:31.785
Look, I'll pay you back
in a month --

22:31.828 --> 22:33.003
You've gotta be
kidding me.

22:33.047 --> 22:34.396
No, i-it's not a lot.
J-Just enough --

22:34.440 --> 22:35.789
These people know where you are
and you came here?

22:35.832 --> 22:37.268
You came to
this house?

22:37.312 --> 22:38.792
Nobody's following me,
if that's what you mean.

22:38.835 --> 22:39.706
Do you know that
for sure?

22:39.749 --> 22:40.968
No, but --

22:41.011 --> 22:41.969
There are children here,
Wendell!

22:42.012 --> 22:43.492
Winston, calm down.

22:44.928 --> 22:45.799
You're putting
my family at risk.

22:45.842 --> 22:47.409
No, I'myour family.

22:47.453 --> 22:53.372
♪♪

22:53.415 --> 22:54.590
Leave tonight.

22:54.634 --> 22:57.550
♪♪

22:57.593 --> 22:59.378
Leave Seattle.
Tonight.

22:59.421 --> 23:04.252
♪♪

23:04.295 --> 23:06.123
Should we...

23:06.167 --> 23:07.298
Eat.

23:14.262 --> 23:16.960
[ Insects chirping,
dog barking in distance ]

23:17.004 --> 23:18.353
[ Footsteps approach ]

23:18.397 --> 23:20.050
Owen:
Hey, uh, here.

23:20.094 --> 23:21.487
Oh, thanks.

23:21.530 --> 23:22.618
I'm sure Amelia
will be back soon.

23:22.662 --> 23:24.185
I'm sorry you got
stuck on kid duty.

23:24.228 --> 23:25.665
[ Chuckling ] Oh, not a problem.
I'm used to it.

23:25.708 --> 23:26.709
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, you got kids?

23:26.753 --> 23:28.145
Uh, niblings.

23:28.189 --> 23:29.146
Nieces and nephews.

23:29.190 --> 23:30.147
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

23:30.191 --> 23:32.062
So do you --
you want kids?

23:32.106 --> 23:34.500
[ Inhales deeply ]
Oh, uh -- [ Sighs ]

23:34.543 --> 23:37.067
Uh, no. No.

23:37.111 --> 23:39.243
My career is my baby.

23:39.287 --> 23:40.636
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

23:40.680 --> 23:41.942
Why, are you trying to unload
one of yours on me?

23:41.985 --> 23:45.162
No, it's just -- you kind
of sound like Amelia,

23:45.206 --> 23:47.382
before she had Scout.
[ Breathes deeply ]

23:47.426 --> 23:49.993
[ Footsteps departing ]

23:51.517 --> 23:55.651
Link: I finally sold
the last one last week.

23:55.695 --> 23:58.349
Poor guy dropped
his first ring in the Sound

23:58.393 --> 24:00.134
while he was proposing.
Mm.

24:00.177 --> 24:02.136
I gave him a good deal.

24:02.179 --> 24:03.790
[ Chuckling ]
Why'd you buy so many?

24:03.833 --> 24:05.052
[ Chuckles ]

24:05.095 --> 24:07.794
I-I used to ask myself
that a lot.

24:07.837 --> 24:09.578
None of the answers
made sense,

24:09.622 --> 24:11.928
so I just tried
to move past it.

24:11.972 --> 24:13.974
How'd that work out?

24:14.017 --> 24:15.802
Um...

24:15.845 --> 24:17.978
I burned my relationship
with Amelia to the ground.

24:18.021 --> 24:19.458
I trashed
my friendship with Jo.

24:19.501 --> 24:21.590
So...not great.

24:21.634 --> 24:23.287
Is it 'cause
you slept together?

24:23.331 --> 24:25.594
I don't regret Scout,
if that's what you mean.

24:25.638 --> 24:27.727
Not Amelia.
Jo.

24:27.770 --> 24:29.598
She told you?

24:29.642 --> 24:31.121
Well, we were drinking.

24:31.165 --> 24:33.384
You say things
when you're drinking.

24:33.428 --> 24:35.212
Did she mention
anything about feelings?

24:35.256 --> 24:37.345
'Cause, apparently,
there were some feelings.

24:37.388 --> 24:38.564
There are
no longer feelings?

24:38.607 --> 24:40.043
Now there's Todd.
Oh.

24:40.087 --> 24:42.611
I-I hardly
see her anymore.

24:42.655 --> 24:44.526
[ Sighs ]
I miss my friend.

24:44.570 --> 24:46.746
But, you know,
I want her to be happy.

24:46.789 --> 24:48.791
And she deserves
the best.

24:48.835 --> 24:50.619
Do you have
feelings for her?

24:51.751 --> 24:53.753
Sometimes.

24:53.796 --> 24:55.537
Maybe, a little.

24:55.581 --> 24:56.886
I'm --

24:56.930 --> 24:58.322
Should I tell her?

24:58.366 --> 25:00.411
That you maybe have
occasional small feelings?

25:00.455 --> 25:01.500
No.

25:01.543 --> 25:03.197
Okay, good.

25:03.240 --> 25:05.547
[ Sighs ]

25:05.591 --> 25:07.027
[ Insects chirping ]

25:07.070 --> 25:08.811
[ Dinnerware clatters lightly ]

25:08.855 --> 25:10.596
Bailey:
The food was delicious.

25:10.639 --> 25:13.599
But this seems like way
more plates than people.

25:13.642 --> 25:15.557
Well, three of those are
the other Bailey's.

25:15.601 --> 25:17.472
[ Sighs ] He doesn't like
his food to touch.

25:17.516 --> 25:20.431
You have cooked and cleaned,
as my guest.

25:20.475 --> 25:22.608
I -- My mother would be
mortified in her grave.

25:22.651 --> 25:24.523
Well, my mom's
probably proud.

25:29.266 --> 25:31.225
Sorry about earlier.

25:31.268 --> 25:35.185
Winston's brother is,
uh, complicated.

25:35.229 --> 25:38.928
Well, complicated people
can be hard to love.

25:40.495 --> 25:44.412
Erica, my younger sister,
she has an uncanny ability

25:44.455 --> 25:46.632
to break my heart
and enrage me all at once.

25:46.675 --> 25:48.808
She's been doing it
for two decades now,

25:48.851 --> 25:50.766
and I-I fall for it
every time.

25:50.810 --> 25:52.202
You see her much?

25:52.246 --> 25:54.553
No. No, I-I don't.
I really don't.

25:54.596 --> 25:57.556
But even when I do, it doesn't
matter if she's sober or not.

25:57.599 --> 25:59.906
She still lies to my face
without an ounce of remorse.

25:59.949 --> 26:02.386
She's
a master manipulator.

26:02.430 --> 26:05.041
Despite all of it, despite
all she's taken from me,

26:05.085 --> 26:08.088
I-I still struggle to say no
when she asks me for something.

26:08.131 --> 26:10.264
Honestly, sometimes
it's the easiest way

26:10.307 --> 26:12.875
just to avoid
another heartbreak.

26:12.919 --> 26:15.312
♪♪

26:15.356 --> 26:16.836
Here.

26:16.879 --> 26:24.452
♪♪

26:24.495 --> 26:32.591
♪♪

26:32.634 --> 26:33.983
[ Door opens ]

26:34.027 --> 26:35.898
[ Telephone rings in distance ]

26:39.119 --> 26:40.599
[ Breathes deeply ]

26:44.646 --> 26:46.082
Are you okay?

26:46.126 --> 26:47.954
Yeah, I'm fine.

26:50.434 --> 26:52.698
[ Door closes ]

26:54.003 --> 26:56.702
[ Sighs ]

26:56.745 --> 26:57.964
[ Door opens ]

26:59.443 --> 27:01.663
[ Plastic crinkles ]

27:01.707 --> 27:03.186
For your hand?

27:03.230 --> 27:06.363
♪♪

27:06.407 --> 27:08.409
Yeah.

27:08.452 --> 27:12.761
♪♪

27:12.805 --> 27:14.633
[ Door closes ]

27:14.676 --> 27:22.379
♪♪

27:22.423 --> 27:30.387
♪♪

27:30.431 --> 27:38.047
♪♪

27:38.091 --> 27:42.617
♪♪

27:44.619 --> 27:46.882
Any of those clinical trials
have success?

27:46.926 --> 27:49.102
The ones I've read
are still ongoing.

27:49.145 --> 27:51.452
Before Simon's diagnosis,
I always thought

27:51.495 --> 27:53.933
that cancer was this thing
that you either beat or didn't.

27:53.976 --> 27:56.718
Like it was a stupid puzzle

27:56.762 --> 27:59.460
and we just needed to find
all the pieces.

27:59.503 --> 28:03.290
But I didn't realize that there
was a third, awful option

28:03.333 --> 28:06.728
where you don't die,
but you don't get rid of it.

28:06.772 --> 28:10.427
You just live with it...

28:10.471 --> 28:12.995
waiting for it to get worse
and praying that it doesn't.

28:14.693 --> 28:15.998
Yeah,
I know the feeling.

28:16.042 --> 28:17.739
For a long time,
I was in denial.

28:17.783 --> 28:20.481
I was sure that Simon
would be the exception.

28:20.524 --> 28:25.399
That we would find a way to
beat the thing that's, uh...

28:25.442 --> 28:27.314
♪♪

28:27.357 --> 28:28.358
Yeah.

28:28.402 --> 28:29.664
♪♪

28:29.708 --> 28:31.274
[ Breathes sharply ]

28:31.318 --> 28:35.061
I think I became obsessed
with us conceiving

28:35.104 --> 28:38.064
because it would mean
that he couldn't die.

28:38.107 --> 28:39.761
There's no way,
right?

28:39.805 --> 28:43.504
God wouldn't kill a man
before his child was born.

28:43.547 --> 28:46.594
♪♪

28:46.637 --> 28:50.293
[ Voice breaking ] I was
so happy when we got pregnant.

28:50.337 --> 28:54.297
So happy that
we'd finally be a family.

28:54.341 --> 28:56.343
♪♪

28:56.386 --> 28:59.520
And then I'd realized that
we'd always been a family.

28:59.563 --> 29:00.826
[ Whispering ]
Me and him.

29:00.869 --> 29:02.741
♪♪

29:02.784 --> 29:08.529
And by not letting him
accept and grieve the fact

29:08.572 --> 29:11.314
that he might not
survive...

29:11.358 --> 29:14.970
♪♪

29:15.014 --> 29:17.364
...I'd left him alone
in it.

29:17.407 --> 29:19.235
♪♪

29:19.279 --> 29:21.324
And no one
wants to be alone.

29:21.368 --> 29:26.677
♪♪

29:26.721 --> 29:28.592
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]Meredith:
What's happening?

29:28.636 --> 29:30.029
She's hypotensive.

29:30.072 --> 29:31.552
Her crits are dropping,
and her belly's distended.

29:31.595 --> 29:33.206
And I'm seeing way more
free fluid than before.

29:33.249 --> 29:34.685
Yeah, her spleen has
probably ruptured.

29:34.729 --> 29:36.383
We need to get her
to the OR -- stat.

29:36.426 --> 29:38.777
Let's call the OR and tell them
we're bringing her down.

29:38.820 --> 29:40.822
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

29:40.866 --> 29:43.651
She's in V-fib. Let's get
the crash cart in here, now!

29:43.694 --> 29:45.522
[ Breathing sharply ]

29:45.566 --> 29:46.654
Come on, come on,
let's go.

29:46.697 --> 29:47.829
Take out
the cut down tray.

29:47.873 --> 29:48.917
We're opening her up
in here?

29:48.961 --> 29:50.179
Yes, we're
opening her up in here.

29:50.223 --> 29:51.354
We're not going to let
her die, Schmitt.

29:51.398 --> 29:53.443
She's not dying.
Charge paddles to 120.

29:53.487 --> 29:54.444
[ Paddles whine ]

29:54.488 --> 29:55.532
Clear.

29:55.576 --> 29:56.838
[ Thump ]

29:56.882 --> 29:58.840
[ Sighs ]
Charge again.

29:58.884 --> 30:00.320
Clear.[ Paddles whine ]

30:00.363 --> 30:01.843
[ Thump ]

30:01.887 --> 30:03.149
♪♪

30:03.192 --> 30:03.932
[ Sighs ]

30:10.504 --> 30:12.201
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

30:12.245 --> 30:13.507
[ Humming ]

30:13.550 --> 30:14.725
[ Vocalizing ]

30:14.769 --> 30:16.684
[ Glove snap echoes ]

30:16.727 --> 30:18.338
[ Vocalizing continues ]

30:18.381 --> 30:24.823
♪♪

30:24.866 --> 30:26.085
[ Rustling sheet echoes ]

30:26.128 --> 30:29.349
♪ My fire is starved of oxygen

30:29.392 --> 30:32.439
♪♪

30:32.482 --> 30:37.357
♪ A flicker in
the howling wind ♪

30:37.400 --> 30:39.925
♪♪

30:39.968 --> 30:44.494
♪ Beware,
the night is closing in ♪

30:44.538 --> 30:47.149
♪♪

30:47.193 --> 30:48.803
♪ And if I fall asleep...

30:48.847 --> 30:49.804
[ Ratcheting echoes ]

30:49.848 --> 30:51.588
♪ ...the shadows win

30:51.632 --> 30:53.242
♪♪

30:53.286 --> 30:55.244
[ Vocalizing ]

30:55.288 --> 31:02.164
♪♪

31:02.208 --> 31:09.215
♪♪

31:09.258 --> 31:14.002
♪ Oh, to sing
and make my mother proud ♪

31:14.046 --> 31:16.875
♪♪

31:16.918 --> 31:19.051
[ Vocalizing ]

31:19.094 --> 31:26.101
♪♪

31:26.145 --> 31:33.239
♪♪

31:33.282 --> 31:38.722
♪ Mm, to sing
and make my mother proud ♪

31:38.766 --> 31:45.512
♪♪

31:45.555 --> 31:50.256
♪ In the dark,
I learned to love again ♪

31:50.299 --> 31:53.172
♪♪

31:53.215 --> 31:57.785
♪ A sacred place
it's always been ♪

31:57.828 --> 32:00.657
♪♪

32:00.701 --> 32:05.793
♪ Where souls depart
and life begins ♪

32:05.836 --> 32:08.361
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

32:08.404 --> 32:12.756
♪ The dark led me
to light again ♪

32:12.800 --> 32:15.150
♪♪

32:15.194 --> 32:21.722
♪ Yeah, the dark led me
to light again ♪

32:21.765 --> 32:23.289
[ Meredith
speaking indistinctly ]

32:23.332 --> 32:26.466
[ Vocalizing ]

32:26.509 --> 32:28.903
♪♪

32:28.947 --> 32:32.080
[ Breathes deeply ]
She is okay.

32:32.124 --> 32:33.473
Oh.

32:33.516 --> 32:35.040
♪♪

32:35.083 --> 32:36.693
Thank you.

32:36.737 --> 32:39.131
We -- We could never
thank you enough.

32:39.174 --> 32:41.220
♪ Yeah, the dark led me
to light again ♪

32:41.263 --> 32:42.917
We still have to monitor her
for the next few days, as well.

32:42.961 --> 32:44.353
Of course.

32:44.397 --> 32:46.486
Popo's okay!
Yay!

32:46.529 --> 32:49.793
♪♪

32:49.837 --> 32:51.665
♪♪

32:51.708 --> 32:53.275
[ Humming ]

32:53.319 --> 32:55.364
[ Vocalizing ]

32:55.408 --> 33:01.501
♪♪

33:01.544 --> 33:03.111
Mm.

33:03.155 --> 33:08.464
♪♪

33:10.423 --> 33:12.599
[ Telephone rings in distance,
indistinct conversations ]

33:12.642 --> 33:14.862
Catherine, honey...

33:14.905 --> 33:16.342
I want you
to live forever.

33:16.385 --> 33:18.039
[ Chuckles ]

33:18.083 --> 33:20.215
And if I could do that with
a surgery, you know I would.

33:20.259 --> 33:22.261
Richard, I can't listen to
another study right now.

33:22.304 --> 33:24.437
No, no -- Just --
Baby,
I can't do it.

33:24.480 --> 33:27.048
What, um --

33:27.092 --> 33:31.096
What I'm gonna say is,
uh...

33:31.139 --> 33:34.490
if you're putting yourself
through this for me, then don't.

33:36.231 --> 33:40.496
If you want to stop,
I'm going to support you.

33:40.540 --> 33:43.847
I don't want to stop
my treatments, baby, no.

33:43.891 --> 33:46.502
It's just --
[ Sighs ]

33:46.546 --> 33:51.507
Sometimes I feel like
I just need time to think.

33:51.551 --> 33:54.075
Like I need to just be able
to live in the moment

33:54.119 --> 33:58.906
without judgment or worrying
about what's next,

33:58.949 --> 34:01.082
even when I'm doing
this chemo.

34:01.126 --> 34:05.695
And you are so serious
all the time,

34:05.739 --> 34:09.221
sometimes that
makes me feel --

34:09.264 --> 34:12.006
sometimes that
makes me feel worse.

34:13.094 --> 34:15.140
Because [chuckles]
a-any one of us

34:15.183 --> 34:18.708
could drop dead tomorrow
from a million different things.

34:18.752 --> 34:22.277
I have cancer,
and that sucks.

34:22.321 --> 34:24.758
But I still
want to live.

34:24.801 --> 34:27.108
I still want to laugh.

34:27.152 --> 34:32.461
♪♪

34:32.505 --> 34:36.509
I-I can come up with a good joke
if you give me a minute.

34:36.552 --> 34:39.338
[ Laughs ]

34:39.381 --> 34:41.731
That's -- mmm.
[ Laughs ]
[ Chuckles ]

34:41.775 --> 34:43.994
That's what I need.

34:44.038 --> 34:46.388
That's what I need.
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

34:46.432 --> 34:48.521
Hey.

34:48.564 --> 34:51.132
Sorry. [ Chuckles ]

34:51.176 --> 34:52.351
Is Scout okay?

34:52.394 --> 34:54.353
Yeah.

34:54.396 --> 34:57.573
Sometimes he just needs
some soothing reassurance.

34:57.617 --> 34:58.966
[ Sighs ]
Takes after his mom.

34:59.009 --> 35:00.098
[ Chuckles ]

35:01.925 --> 35:06.408
Your family and friends
seem like good people.

35:06.452 --> 35:08.323
They are.

35:08.367 --> 35:12.371
You'll see,
once you get to know them.

35:12.414 --> 35:16.157
And I promise Scout
is not always this fussy.

35:18.203 --> 35:21.162
He became real
to me tonight,

35:21.206 --> 35:24.034
because I got to see what an
amazing parent you are to him.

35:24.078 --> 35:25.340
And to
Meredith's kids.

35:25.384 --> 35:27.516
You are so much more
than just an aunt.

35:27.560 --> 35:29.127
Mm.

35:31.781 --> 35:33.827
I don't want kids,
though.

35:35.263 --> 35:38.179
I have things I want
to do with my life...

35:38.223 --> 35:41.487
professionally
and personally.

35:41.530 --> 35:43.837
If I had kids, all of that
would have to come second.

35:43.880 --> 35:46.056
I don't want to
do that.

35:46.100 --> 35:48.058
Well, y-you've
told me that before --

35:48.102 --> 35:50.800
I am not going to
change my mind, Amelia.

35:50.844 --> 35:52.541
Ever.

35:52.585 --> 35:54.326
♪♪

35:54.369 --> 35:55.501
W-What...

35:55.544 --> 35:58.547
♪♪

35:58.591 --> 36:00.375
What does that mean?

36:00.419 --> 36:03.161
♪♪

36:03.204 --> 36:06.294
I thought this
was going really well.

36:06.338 --> 36:08.862
Yeah, I did, too.

36:08.905 --> 36:10.559
And I don't know.

36:10.603 --> 36:13.127
♪♪

36:13.171 --> 36:15.085
I just know
I don't want to lead you on.

36:15.129 --> 36:16.739
♪♪

36:16.783 --> 36:18.959
Because I was once
led on by someone

36:19.002 --> 36:22.049
who did not want
what I did.

36:22.092 --> 36:29.230
♪♪

36:29.274 --> 36:31.276
Oh, I needed that.
[ Sighs ]

36:31.319 --> 36:32.364
[ Chuckles ]

36:32.407 --> 36:34.670
I had fun.

36:34.714 --> 36:37.804
You know, despite
what you all think,

36:37.847 --> 36:39.675
I know fun.
[ Chuckles ]

36:39.719 --> 36:41.590
I will never doubt it again.[ Car beeps ]

36:41.634 --> 36:44.376
[ Chuckles ]

36:44.419 --> 36:45.464
Hi.

36:45.507 --> 36:46.856
Hey.

36:46.900 --> 36:49.119
Mm. Mmm.

36:49.163 --> 36:51.252
Mmm.
Mmm.

36:51.296 --> 36:53.298
Mmm.
Mmm.

36:53.341 --> 36:54.690
Hey, are we --
Mm-hmm.

36:54.734 --> 36:56.431
Really?
Mm-hmm.

36:56.475 --> 36:57.389
Okay.
[ Laughs ]

36:57.432 --> 37:00.087
Alright. Okay.

37:00.130 --> 37:01.262
Come here.

37:01.306 --> 37:03.046
[ Laughs ][ Clattering ]

37:03.090 --> 37:05.266
Owen: It's good.[ Laughing ]

37:05.310 --> 37:06.572
Mm.
Come on, now.Oh!

37:06.615 --> 37:08.313
You people are parents.

37:08.356 --> 37:10.315
[ Both laugh ]

37:10.358 --> 37:12.621
Come here. Mmm.[ Laughs ]

37:16.059 --> 37:18.453
Wendell left
about 45 minutes ago.

37:18.497 --> 37:19.715
Yeah, I'm sorry
I walked out.

37:19.759 --> 37:20.803
I just --
I needed a minute.

37:20.847 --> 37:22.979
And I'm sorry that
he showed up here

37:23.023 --> 37:24.154
when he's
in so much trouble.

37:24.198 --> 37:25.591
If I had known that he
had people --

37:25.634 --> 37:27.723
Winston, I'm not worried about
Wendell or his lenders.

37:27.767 --> 37:29.203
[ Breathes deeply ]

37:29.247 --> 37:31.510
I gave him the money
to pay them back.

37:31.553 --> 37:34.252
I really wish you hadn't
done that, Maggie.
[ Sighs ]

37:34.295 --> 37:36.166
I know, I know, I know.
I should have asked you first.

37:36.210 --> 37:37.342
It's not your place
to pay him --

37:37.385 --> 37:39.822
You're right.

37:39.866 --> 37:43.348
$10,000 is a lot of money,
but I had the savings

37:43.391 --> 37:45.698
and he's
my family now, too, so...

37:45.741 --> 37:48.222
Maggie. Maggie.

37:48.266 --> 37:50.529
I gave him
the money, too.

37:50.572 --> 37:52.095
♪♪

37:52.139 --> 37:53.793
[ Sighing ]

37:53.836 --> 37:56.317
Meredith: Microbes may sound
like uninvited guests...

37:56.361 --> 37:58.101
♪♪

37:58.145 --> 37:59.755
